Hi 

Right now the code macro does not have highlighting for JQL

Can we have it included, especially since JQL is not know widely outside users of Atlassian products, many times it needs to be shown. The best workaround now is SQL and it dosent highlight things like project, cf, changed and other JQL keywords
{code:java}

project = XX and status changed from "STATUSA" to "STATUSB" after -1d {code}

Currently these two APIs take a callback function as the only parameter, to access the macro parameters/body returned, e.g.

AP.confluence.getMacroBody(body => {
  // do something with macro body
});

It would be ergonomic if (like AP.request), when the callback is omitted, they return a promise that resolves to the returned value.

This would enable async/await such as:

const body = await AP.confluence.getMacroBody();
